// Alien weapons, currently:
//	plaspistol
//	plaspistol_ammo
//	plasrifle
//	plasrifle_ammo
//	plasblaster
//	plasblaster_ammo
//	tachyonpistol
//	tachyonpistol_ammo
//	tachyonrifle
//	tachyonrifle_ammo
//	tachyonsniper
//	tachyonsniper_ammo
//	kerrblade
//	plasblade
//	alienincgrenade
//	plasmagrenade
//
// The equipment approximately represent what an 8-alien team
// will have on battlescape. This is also the loot you get
// from auto-mission with 8 aliens. If there are n < 8 aliens,
// you get only n/8 of each item number, rounded down
// (the rounding down is the auto-mission penalty).
//
// Alien weapon assignment procedure.
// For each alien, pick the following:
// 1. the most expensive primary weapon W with probability #W/8
//    where #W is the number of W weapons listed in equipment
// 1a. if still no primary weapon,
//     the second most expensive primary weapon X with probability #X/8
// etc. for all primary weapons (the order is essential);
// keep the total <= 8 or the theoretical loot will
// be much higher than the actual loot
// 2. similary, sidearms (secondary weapons with reload) based on price, 
//    so in case of current weapons this is:
//    tachyonpistol with probability #tachyonpistol/8
// 2a. if still no sidearm,
//     plaspistol with probability #plaspistol/8;
//     add some bonus to probability for those aliens
//     that don't have primary weapons, yet,
//     and some malus to those that already have,
//     with decent probability of akimbo, too;
//     moreover alien with tachyon primary weapon 
//     will start picking sidarm with plaspistol, not tachyonpistol;
//     keep the total <= 8, likewise
// 3. get the following number of ammo for each weapon separately:
//      (#ammo/#weapon) slightly randomly increased
//    with probability depending on the fractional part,
//    where #ammo and #weapon are the numbers of that particular
//    ammo and weapon in the equipment definition;
//    #ammo/#weapon should be greater than 1
// 4. for each misc item (alienincgrenade or plasmagrenade)
//    and secondary weapon without reload (kerrblade or plasblade) get
//      (#item/8) slightly randomly increased
//    with probability depending on the fractional part
//    for each alien (as long as it fits in the backpack);
//    the order is from the most expensive to the least expensive;
//    add some bonus to probability for those aliens
//    that don't have primary weapons nor sidearms, yet,
//    and some malus to those that already have

// There is no problem if the number of assigned things
// is bigger than the total in equipment --- on average it is OK.
// For example, take 8-alien team, then 1 plasrifle
// makes it possible, though very unlikely, that each alien
// will get a rifle. Take a 5-alien team with 8 plasrifles,
// this guarantees that each alien will get a primary weapon;
// with 12 plasrifle_ammo, they will also get, on average, 1.5 ammo per alien.
// but with 2-alien team, 7 plasrifle gives only high probability
// that there will be at least 1 plasrifle in the team, no certainty.
// Each individual type of misc items and blades is assigned separately,
// so e.g., 8 alienincgrenade and 8 plasmagrenade gives two grenades per alien,
// on average, while 8 plaspistol and 8 tachyonpistol gives only 1 sidearm
// (so 4 plaspistol and 4 tachyonpistol is a better idea in practice).

